shared_text:
USD 466 School Health
August 20 at 9:13 PM ·

‼️Attention parents‼️We need your help! We need your help to do a quick check of your children before sending them to school everyday. We want to ensure that every one arrives at school healthy and ready to learn! Please, take a look at the attached picture for symptoms to look for and instructions. Any children that arrive with signs or symptoms that look like COVID (and aren’t caused by other conditions) and/or may have been exposed may be sent home for evaluation.

Teachers and student are considered Essential Workers. See the attached picture that describes the process that we will follow in the case of an exposed teacher or student without symptoms. We will of course ultimately follow the directions provided to us by the Health Department. You can also click the link for the complete KDHE guidance @ https://www.coronavirus.kdheks.gov/DocumentCenter/View/1377/Guidance-for-Modified-Quarantine-in-K-12-Schools---7-28-2020

post_text:
IMPORTANT MESSAGE:

Teens have a great deal of time on their hands right now. Although we would like to think they are using this time to read more, journal, and maybe research possible careers and colleges, that is likely not the sole scenario. Sadly, this is a prime time for bad decision making and less than thoughtful behavior. Please warn your teens that unsavory characters may try to access personal information and/or social media accounts. Remind your teens to never give out any personal information, even to friends, regarding passwords, birthdates, social security numbers, etc. It is simply too easy for accounts to be hacked or stolen with just one little mistake. “Think before you respond to that seemingly innocent request; you really do not know who is on the other end.”

Announcement March 13, 2020
Given the escalating concerns regarding COVID-19 and the closures of schools and school host sites, all Regional Music Festivals scheduled for March 28 and April 4 have been cancelled and will not be rescheduled. The KSHSAA deeply regrets these lost opportunities, but it is the best decision for the safety of our students, directors, adjudicators and spectators.

Note: All other 2020 KSHSAA music festival or KSHSAA speech tournament dates have not been cancelled at this time including State Music Festivals for solos and small ensembles. More information will be given as it becomes available.

Please be safe,
Craig

Craig L. Manteuffel

post_text: Our local Police department patch contest was a huge success! The have narrowed down the choices to their finalists. Several officers will be at the varsity basketball game on Friday asking the community to help us pick the winner. Each patch will have a bucket to collect funds. The patch with the most money in it will be declared the winner. All funds raised on this night will be donated to the Western Kansas Child Advocacy Center. This is an incredible non profit organization that we work with almost daily. The WKCAC provides services to 33 counties in the western part of the state. Come out and enjoy the final home basketball game versus Holcomb and pick your favorite patch. This will be an opportunity to raise some money for a great cause and you can meet some officers, including the Chief!
